{
  "stem": "8679.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I wore it with pride.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never attached to it the word 'shame.' They called it a 'badge of shame.' To me it was a-- a badge of honor-- absolutely.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nobody felt ashamed about it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was really plain to see who was to be-- who should be ashamed-- definitely not us, the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It put-- you got more scared because from far on the street you could see, point out, there's a Jew walking.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, uh, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "With us, they didn't accomplish that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They put the shame on themselves.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Hitler came in March 1938.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In November-- November 9, 1938, a government-incited riot took place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was the idea of the government.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The streets-- all the stores of the Jewish-- the-- the windows of the stores of Jewish people were smashed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Before, they had all to have a sign painted on it, 'Jew.' They were smashed, the glass littering the street.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's why they came up to call it Kristallnacht, the Night of the Broken Glass.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "All our synagogues went up in flames, and Jews were rounded up and taken to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In some cases, nobody can believe the cruelty.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They sometimes sent home a package containing the ashes and requesting to whoever got the box with ashes of their loved one to pay five schilling.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "A, Jews don't believe in cremation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "B, you really never knew whether those were the ashes of your loved one.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But you had to pay up to get it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All of it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All of it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was on the street running home, running home, like for my life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there we sat, huddled together.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And from the window, you could see the flames rising of the synagogues.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, because my father wasn't taken away.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
